dress><Description><![CDATA[<p>Trust-IT Sweden AB has adopted Infoglue CMS to their web hosting solution! And are from now on offering all their customer a good and reliable CMS solution.</p> <p>Trust-IT was founded in mars 1997, and is currently working with three different business legs, Tech, Education and Development! And Infoglue CMS is handled in Trust-IT tech department.</p> <p>For further information please visit our official web site, unfortunately it is currently only in Swedish, however, if you have any questions regarding Infoglue CMS hosting, please send an email to: <a href=\"mailto:igcms@trustit.se\">igcms@trustit.se</a></p>]]></Description><Category><![CDATA[]]></Category></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:12:11','No comment',0,1,261,1,'mattias'),(229,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><CompanyName><![CDATA[Tripnet AB]]></CompanyName><SiteAddress><![CDATA[http://www.tripnet.se]]></SiteAddress><Description><![CDATA[<p>Tripnet AB is a Swedish hosting provider founded in 1995. We are focused on high quality services for companies with high demands. We were the first hosting partner providing Infoglue CMS hosting. We also have established business relations with one of the initial developers of InfoGlue, Sprawl Solutions.</p> <p>In addition to the Infoglue CMS web hosting service, Tripnet also provide datacenter services such as managed hosting of dedicated servers, backup, firewall administration, DNS and e-mail services. For futher information please visit our website, send an email to: <a href=\"mailto:sales@tripnet.se\">sales@tripnet.se</a> or call us on +46 31 725 25 00.</p>]]></Description><Category><![CDATA[]]></Category></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:12:11','No comment',0,1,262,1,'mattias'),(230,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><CompanyName><![CDATA[Novanet]]></CompanyName><SiteAddress><![CDATA[http://novanet.ch]]></SiteAddress><Description><![CDATA[<p>Novanet Provides Design, Hosting and Professional Services based on open J2EE Architectures (Infoglue / Apache / IBM Websphere) IG-Site Example: http://www.pss-technology.com/<br /><br />Contact: <a href=\"mailto:mpuetz@novanet.ch\">mpuetz@novanet.ch</a></p>]]></Description><Category><![CDATA[Hosting]]></Category></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:12:11','No comment',0,1,263,1,'mattias'),(231,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><CompanyName><![CDATA[ARTSYS]]></CompanyName><SiteAddress><![CDATA[http://www.artsys.fr]]></SiteAddress><Description><![CDATA[<p>Internet and Java/JEE solution provider. Based in Paris, France.</p><br />]]></Description><Category><![CDATA[SolutionProvider]]></Category></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:12:12','No comment',0,1,264,1,'mattias'),(232,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><CompanyName><![CDATA[Ahead of the Curve]]></CompanyName><SiteAddress><![CDATA[www.aheadofthecurve.com.au]]></SiteAddress><Description><![CDATA[<p>Ahead of the Curve (AOTC) is an Australian based digital and design agency specialising in a broad range of next generation technologies that reduce costs, boost revenues, streamline processes and generally make life at your company easier for customers, staff and suppliers.</p>]]></Description><Category><![CDATA[SolutionProvider]]></Category></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:12:12','No comment',0,1,265,1,'mattias'),(233,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Help resources]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Help resources]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<h3>User Help</h3> <ul>     <li>The most informative and&nbsp;complete&nbsp;manual currently available are located in the <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(75, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">documentation</a> area. The user manual covers all tools extensively as well as explains the fundamentals behind InfoGlue while the administrative manual explains everything there is to know about setting up and managing the system.</li> </ul> <h3>Developer help</h3> <ul>     <li>There are some resources(pdf, video etc) in the <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(75, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">documentation</a> section.</li>     <li>Check out the Confluence part of <a href=\"http://www.infoglue.org\">www.infoglue.org</a></li>     <li>Use the mailing lists and the forums.</li>     <li>A developer manual for InfoGlue 2.3 is also available on the marketplace for a small sum <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(72, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here</a>.</li> </ul> <h3>Support options or sponsored development</h3> <ul>     <li>If you feel InfoGlue is a good start but needs some additional features or you need professional support for it please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:info@infoglue.org\">info@infoglue.org</a> and we will direct you to a recommended developer/company.</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[This page will try to sum up all resources and options available to users and developers looking for help resources. As the work progress we will hopefully put a online manual here but until then other alternatives are listed below.]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:08','Ny namnstandard',0,1,267,1,'mattias'),(234,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Downloads]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Downloads]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>This section contains downloads of all software maintained by the InfoGlue Community. The community has grown and now contains several software packages and components. Because of this we have divided the download area in different areas.</p><ul><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(35, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue WCMS</a> - the main software - a great CMS / Portal system</li><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(36, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue Calendar</a> - a portlet-based event calendar</li><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(37, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue Eclipse IDE</a> - a vital eclipse plugin for all InfoGlue developers.</li></ul><p>Additional downloads like site exports and individual components can be found under the <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(40, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">developer pages</a>.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[Downloads]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:25','Ny namnstandard',0,1,270,1,'mattias'),(235,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Calendar downloads]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Calendar downloads]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=73706\">Download the official version of InfoGlue Calendar Portlet here</a><br /> After you have downloaded the package you should follow the installation instructions found <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(27, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here.</a></p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[Calendar downloads]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-24 23:05:18','Published calendar war',0,1,271,1,'mattias'),(236,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[InfoGlue Eclipse IDE download]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[InfoGlue Eclipse IDE download]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>The InfoGlue Eclipse IDE exits as a jar-file (can be fetched <a href=\"http://www.infoglue.org/downloads/igide/plugins/org.infoglue.igide_0.8.1.jar\">here</a>) but since Eclipse has such a great installation mechanism you should definately use the installation method described <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(29, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here</a>.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:24','Ny namnstandard',0,1,272,1,'mattias'),(237,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[InfoGlue WCMS Download]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[InfoGlue WCMS Download]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p><a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=73706\" target=\"_blank\">Download the official version of InfoGlue here</a><br /> After you have downloaded the package you should follow the installation instructions found in the zipfile or the one found <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(17, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here</a>.</p> <p>In addition you can find nightly builds <a href=\"http://www.infoglue.org/downloads\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. We strongly recommend you not to use these versions in production. Often they may not work at all depending on the state of development. Using them is at your own risk as usual.</p> <p>For information about how to get the source and build InfoGlue look at our <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(85, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\" target=\"_blank\">CVS-page</a></p> <p>For documentation of the platform look at the document section under products <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(75, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here</a>.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[Welcome to the download section. We have decided to utilize the sourceforge facilities for distributing InfoGlue for now.]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:25','Ny namnstandard',0,1,273,1,'mattias'),(238,2,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><UserInputHTML><![CDATA[#macro(listChildContents $parentContentId)\r\n  #if(!$childContent.isBranch)\r\n     <tr>\r\n        <td colspan=\"2\"><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"150\" value=\"$parentContentId\">$scriptLogic.getContentController().getContentVOWithId($parentContentId).name</td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  #end\r\n\r\n  #foreach($childContent in $scriptLogic.getContentController().getContentChildren($parentContentId))\r\n\r\n    #if(!$childContent.isBranch)\r\n    <tr>\r\n        <td colspan=\"2\"><input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"150\" value=\"$childContent.id\">$childContent.name</td>\r\n      </tr>\r\n    #end\r\n\r\n    #if($childContent.isBranch)\r\n      #listChildContents($childContent.id)\r\n    #end\r\n  #end\r\n#end \r\n\r\n<html>\r\n<head>\r\n  <title>Export content</title>\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"css/cms.css\" /> \r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"pragma\" CONTENT=\"no-cache\" />\r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"expires\" CONTENT=\"-1\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />	\r\n	\r\n  <script language=\"JavaScript\"> \r\n    window.resizeTo(400,600);\r\n  </script> \r\n	\r\n</head>\r\n<body class=\"contenttooledit\">\r\n<form name=\"inputForm\" method=\"get\" action=\"ViewExecuteTask!executeTask.action\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"taskContentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"taskContentId\")\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"contentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td class=\"actionheader\" colspan=\"2\">XML Export Content</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">This task lets you select wich contents you want to export in the folder you marked before executing the task. The contents will be exported to a common transfer format of InfoGlue. This makes it possible for anybody to import it on another infoglue instance anywhere.</td> \r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td>State which languages you wish to include in the export</td>\r\n  <td>\r\n    #foreach ($languageVO in $scriptLogic.getLanguageController().getLanguageVOList($scriptLogic.database))\r\n        <input type=\"checkbox\" name=\"languageId\" value=\"$languageVO.getLanguageId()\">$languageVO.getName()\r\n    #end\r\n  </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td>What version do you want to export</td>\r\n  <td><input type=\"radio\" name=\"method\" value=\"published\" checked=\"1\"> Published versions<br> <input type=\"radio\" name=\"method\" value=\"working\"> Latest versions\r\n  </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">State which contents you wish to export</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n#listChildContents($scriptLogic.getInteger($scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")))\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Export\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>]]></UserInputHTML><ScriptCode><![CDATA[#macro(exportContent $contentId $languageIdArray)\r\n  \r\n  #set($contentController = $scriptLogic.getContentController())\r\n  #set($currentContent = $contentController.getContentWithId($contentId, $scriptLogic.database))  \r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"currentContent:\", $currentContent)\r\n\r\n  #set($contentTypeDefinitionName = $currentContent.contentTypeDefinition.name))\r\n\r\n  #set($method = $scriptLogic.getRequest().getParameter(\"method\"))\r\n  \r\n  #set($contentElement = $domBuilder.addElement($contentsElement, \"content\"))\r\n  $domBuilder.addAttribute($contentElement, \"contentId\", \"$contentId\")\r\n  $domBuilder.addAttribute($contentElement, \"name\", \"$currentContent.name\")\r\n  \r\n  #if($contentTypeDefinitionName)\r\n  	$domBuilder.addAttribute($contentElement, \"contentTypeDefinitionName\", \"$!contentTypeDefinitionName\")\r\n  #end\r\n  \r\n  #foreach($languageIdString in $languageIdArray)\r\n  	  #set($languageId = $scriptLogic.getInteger($languageIdString))\r\n      $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"contentId:\", $contentId)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"languageId:\", $languageId)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"contentId:\", $contentId.class.getName())\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"db:\", $scriptLogic.database)\r\n	\r\n	  #if($method == \"published\")\r\n	\r\n	    #if(!$scriptLogic.isNull($scriptLogic.getContentVersionController().getLatestPublishedContentVersion($contentId, $languageId)))\r\n	\r\n	      #set($contentVersionElement = $domBuilder.addElement($contentElement, \"contentVersion\"))\r\n	      \r\n	      $domBuilder.addAttribute($contentVersionElement, \"languageId\", \"$languageId\")\r\n	     \r\n	      #set($contentVersionVO = $scriptLogic.getContentVersionController().getLatestPublishedContentVersion($contentId, $languageId))\r\n		  \r\n	      #set($versionDocument = $domBuilder.getDocument($contentVersionVO.versionValue))\r\n	      $domBuilder.insertElement($contentVersionElement, $versionDocument.getRootElement())\r\n	    #end\r\n	\r\n	  #else\r\n	\r\n	    #if(!$scriptLogic.isNull($scriptLogic.getContentVersionController().getLatestActiveContentVersionVO($contentId, $languageId)))\r\n	\r\n	      #set($contentVersionElement = $domBuilder.addElement($contentElement, \"contentVersion\"))\r\n	      \r\n	      $domBuilder.addAttribute($contentVersionElement, \"languageId\", \"$languageId\")\r\n	\r\n	      #set($contentVersionVO = $scriptLogic.getContentVersionController().getLatestActiveContentVersionVO($contentId, $languageId))\r\n		\r\n	      #set($versionDocument = $domBuilder.getDocument($contentVersionVO.versionValue))\r\n	      $domBuilder.insertElement($contentVersionElement, $versionDocument.getRootElement())\r\n	    #end\r\n	\r\n	  #end\r\n  #end\r\n#end\r\n\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"******************************\")\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"** Running task Export Content   **\")\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"******************************\")\r\n\r\n#set($languageIdArray = $scriptLogic.getRequest().getParameterValues(\"languageId\"))\r\n#set($contents = $scriptLogic.getRequest().getParameterValues(\"150\"))\r\n\r\n#foreach($contentId in $contents)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo($contentId)\r\n#end\r\n\r\n#set($date = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"java.util.Date\"))\r\n#set($cmsPropertyHandler = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.util.CmsPropertyHandler\"))\r\n#set($domBuilder = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.util.dom.DOMBuilder\"))\r\n#set($document = $domBuilder.createDocument())\r\n\r\n#set($rootElement = $domBuilder.addElement($document, \"export\"))\r\n\r\n$domBuilder.addAttribute($rootElement , \"exportDateTime\", $date.toString())\r\n\r\n#set($contentsElement= $domBuilder.addElement($rootElement , \"contents\"))\r\n  \r\n#foreach($contentId in $contents)\r\n  ##exportContent($scriptLogic.getInteger($contentId) $scriptLogic.getInteger($languageId))\r\n  #exportContent($scriptLogic.getInteger($contentId) $languageIdArray)\r\n#end\r\n\r\n#set($exportFileName = \"export_$date.getYear()-$date.getMonth()-$date.getDate()_${date.getTime()}.xml\")\r\n#set($exportFileUrl = \"$cmsPropertyHandler.getProperty(\'webServerAddress\')/$cmsPropertyHandler.getProperty(\'digitalAssetBaseUrl\')/$exportFileName\")\r\n\r\n#set($fileName = \"$cmsPropertyHandler.getProperty(\'digitalAssetPath\')/export_$date.getYear()-$date.getMonth()-$date.getDate()_${date.getTime()}.xml\")\r\n$domBuilder.write($document, $fileName)\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.setOutputParameter(\"exportFileName\", $exportFileName)\r\n$scriptLogic.setOutputParameter(\"exportFileUrl\", $exportFileUrl)\r\n\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Export finished\")]]></ScriptCode><UserOutputHTML><![CDATA[<html>\r\n<head>\r\n  <title>Export finished</title>\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"css/cms.css\" /> \r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"pragma\" CONTENT=\"no-cache\" />\r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"expires\" CONTENT=\"-1\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />	\r\n	\r\n  <script language=\"JavaScript\"> \r\n    window.resizeTo(400,600);\r\n  </script> \r\n	\r\n</head>\r\n<body class=\"contenttooledit\">\r\n<form name=\"inputForm\" method=\"get\" action=\"ViewExecuteTask!executeTask.action\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"contentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td class=\"actionheader\" colspan=\"2\">XML Content Export</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">The export was successful and the resulting xml-file is available by clicking on the link below. Rightclick on the link and choose save as if you want to store it locally:<br><br> <b>Download:</b> <a href=\"$scriptLogic.getOutputParameter(\"exportFileUrl\")\">$scriptLogic.getOutputParameter(\"exportFileName\")</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"javascript:window.close();\">Close</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>]]></UserOutputHTML></attributes></article>','2004-02-15 00:00:00','Updated for the new site layout',0,1,274,1,'mattias'),(239,2,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><UserInputHTML><![CDATA[<html>\r\n<head>  \r\n  <title>Import Contents</title>\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"css/cms.css\" /> \r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"pragma\" CONTENT=\"no-cache\" />\r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"expires\" CONTENT=\"-1\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />	\r\n	\r\n  <script language=\"JavaScript\"> \r\n    window.resizeTo(400,600);\r\n  </script> \r\n	\r\n</head>\r\n<body class=\"contenttooledit\">\r\n<form enctype=\"multipart/form-data\" name=\"inputForm\" method=\"post\" action=\"ViewExecuteTask!executeTask.action\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"taskContentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"taskContentId\")\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"contentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td class=\"actionheader\" colspan=\"2\">Content Import</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">This task lets you import contents previously exported to XML. It will import the contents to the folder you stood on when you clicked execute task.</td> \r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">Point out the xml-file that contain the exported contents</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\"><input type=\"file\" name=\"xmlFile\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Import\"></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>]]></UserInputHTML><ScriptCode><![CDATA[#macro(createContent $parentContentId $name $contentTypeDefinitionName $repositoryId $isBranch)\r\n\r\n  #set($contentTypeDefinitionController = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.controllers.kernel.impl.simple.ContentTypeDefinitionController\"))\r\n\r\n  #foreach($contentTypeDefinition in $contentTypeDefinitionController.contentTypeDefinitionVOList)\r\n    #if($contentTypeDefinition.name == \"$contentTypeDefinitionName\")\r\n      #set($contentTypeDefinitionId = $contentTypeDefinition.id)\r\n    #end\r\n  #end\r\n\r\n  #set($newContentVO = $contentController.getNewVO())\r\n  $newContentVO.setName($name)\r\n  $newContentVO.setIsBranch($isBranch)\r\n  \r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $scriptLogic.database)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $parentContentId)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $contentTypeDefinitionId)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $repositoryId)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $newContentVO)\r\n\r\n  #set($newContent = $contentController.create($scriptLogic.database, $parentContentId, $contentTypeDefinitionId, \"$remoteUser\", $repositoryId, $newContentVO))\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"content created:\", $newContent)\r\n\r\n#end\r\n\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"***********************************\")\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"** Running task Import Content   **\")\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"***********************************\")\r\n\r\n#set($remoteUser = $scriptLogic.getRequest().getRemoteUser())\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"remoteUser:\", $remoteUser)\r\n\r\n#set($fileUploadHelper = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.util.FileUploadHelper\"))\r\n#set($file = $fileUploadHelper.getUploadedFile($scriptLogic.getActionContext().getMultiPartRequest()))\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"File:\", $file.getName())\r\n\r\n#set($domBuilder = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.util.dom.DOMBuilder\"))\r\n#set($importDocument = $domBuilder.getDocument($file))\r\n$domBuilder.writeDebug($importDocument)\r\n\r\n#set($contentElements = $importDocument.selectNodes(\"//content\"))\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Contents\", $contentElements.size())\r\n\r\n#set($parentContentId = $scriptLogic.getInteger($scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")))\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"ParentContentId:\", $parentContentId)\r\n\r\n#set($contentController = $scriptLogic.getContentController())\r\n#set($parentContent = $contentController.getContentWithId($parentContentId, $scriptLogic.database))  \r\n#set($repositoryId = $parentContent.repository.id)\r\n\r\n#foreach($contentElement in $contentElements)\r\n  #set($contentId = $contentElement.attribute(\"contentId\").getValue())\r\n  #set($name = $contentElement.attribute(\"name\").getValue())\r\n  #set($contentTypeDefinitionName = $contentElement.attribute(\"contentTypeDefinitionName\").getValue())\r\n\r\n  #set($isFolder = true)\r\n  #if($contentTypeDefinitionName)\r\n  	#set($isFolder = false)\r\n  #end\r\n  	\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"ContentId:\", $contentId)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Name:\", $name)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"ContentTypeDefinitionName:\", $contentTypeDefinitionName)\r\n	\r\n  #createContent($parentContentId $name $contentTypeDefinitionName $repositoryId $isFolder)\r\n  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Content created:\", $newContent.contentId)\r\n\r\n  #foreach($contentVersionElement in $contentElement.elements(\"contentVersion\"))\r\n	  #set($languageId = $contentVersionElement.attribute(\"languageId\").getValue())\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"LanguageId:\", $languageId)\r\n	\r\n	  #set($newContentVersionVO = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"org.infoglue.cms.entities.content.ContentVersionVO\"))\r\n	  #set($date = $scriptLogic.getObjectWithName(\"java.util.Date\"))\r\n	  $newContentVersionVO.setLanguageId($languageId)\r\n	  $newContentVersionVO.setStateId(0)\r\n	  $newContentVersionVO.setModifiedDateTime($date)\r\n	  $newContentVersionVO.setVersionComment(\"Imported\")\r\n	  #set($versionValue = $domBuilder.encodeString($contentVersionElement.elements().get(0).asXML(), \"UTF-8\"))\r\n	  $newContentVersionVO.setVersionValue(\"<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?>$versionValue\")\r\n	\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Adding version as follows\", $newContent.contentId)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"languageId\", $languageId)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"languageId\", $languageId.class.name)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"remoteUser\", $remoteUser)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"newContentVersionVO\", $newContentVersionVO)\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"database\", $scriptLogic.database)\r\n	\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"version\", $newContentVersionVO.versionValue)\r\n	  \r\n	  #set($newContentVersion = $scriptLogic.getContentVersionController().create($newContent.contentId, $scriptLogic.getInteger($languageId), \"$remoteUser\", $newContentVersionVO, null, $scriptLogic.database))\r\n	\r\n	  $scriptLogic.logInfo(\"ContentVersion created:\", $newContentVersion.contentVersionId)\r\n  #end\r\n  \r\n#end\r\n\r\n$scriptLogic.logInfo(\"Import finished\")\r\n]]></ScriptCode><UserOutputHTML><![CDATA[<html>\r\n<head>\r\n  <title>Import finished</title>\r\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"css/cms.css\" /> \r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"pragma\" CONTENT=\"no-cache\" />\r\n  <META HTTP-EQUIV=\"expires\" CONTENT=\"-1\" />\r\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\" />	\r\n	\r\n  <script language=\"JavaScript\"> \r\n    window.resizeTo(400,600);\r\n  </script> \r\n	\r\n</head>\r\n<body class=\"contenttooledit\">\r\n<form name=\"inputForm\" method=\"get\" action=\"ViewExecuteTask!executeTask.action\">\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"contentId\" value=\"$scriptLogic.request.getParameter(\"contentId\")\">\r\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\" class=\"actionheader\">Content Import</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">The import was successful</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n  <td colspan=\"2\"><a href=\"javascript:window.close();\">Close</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n</form>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>]]></UserOutputHTML></attributes></article>','2004-02-15 00:00:00','Updated for the new site layout',0,1,275,1,'mattias'),(240,0,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Complete sites]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Complete sites]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>This section is quite small at the moment as it is quite new. Hopefully more people want to share their work or offer them for a price.</p><p>The first site export we have added is of course the export of the InfoGlue.org-site. In contains the entire site including components, structure and contents. It is a very good template to start from when building a new site.</p><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(276, \"export\")\"><img vspace=\"10\" hspace=\"10\" border=\"1\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(285, \"siteDump\")\" alt=\"\" /></a></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Download the xml-export <a href=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(276, \"export\")\">here</a> and look at the user manual for how to install it in your own installation.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-24 23:12:13','New working version',0,1,276,1,'mattias'),(241,0,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Site TODO]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Site TODO]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>What is left</p><ul><li>G&aring; igenom alla texter och komplettera</li></ul><p>Low prio</p><ul><li>&Ouml;vers&auml;tt labels</li><li>&Ouml;vers&auml;tt till svenska</li><li>Inloggning och registration etc</li><li>InfoGlue-loggan</li><li>Snyggare sitemap</li><li>Chat inbyggd</li><li>Kommentera-funktionen - skall den visas j&auml;mt?</li><li>Forum</li><li>Kalendern</li></ul>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:38:58','No comment',0,1,277,1,'mattias'),(242,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Help us keep InfoGlue going]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Donate]]></NavigationTitle><Leadin><![CDATA[InfoGlue is free and is built upon other free software. We in the team work on the project as volunteers and without pay. Sometimes we can develop features while working with customers using InfoGlue but most often we develop the platform on our spare time because we think it\'s fun. ]]></Leadin><FullText><![CDATA[<P>Having this said we also need to support the project with infrastructure and support. At the moment Tripnet is kind enough to host our servers free of charge but we still have to keep up with hardware for the public site, some software upgrades once in a while and new books to keep up to date with new techniques. Finally - even though the participants in the project never will get rich on the platform small encouragements are often enough to keep the spirit up. </P>\r\n<P>So - if you don\'t want to contribute actively in the project but still want to show your apprechiation for what the team is doing you can donate a small sum to us. We will list all donators on the site to give them due credit. </P>\r\n<P>To donate just click on the paypal-icon below </P>\r\n<FORM action=https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr method=post><INPUT type=hidden value=_xclick name=cmd> <INPUT type=hidden value=broker@infoglue.org name=business> <INPUT type=hidden value=InfoGlue name=item_name> <INPUT type=hidden value=InfoGlue name=item_number> <INPUT type=hidden value=1 name=no_note> <INPUT type=hidden value=USD name=currency_code> <INPUT type=hidden value=0 name=tax> <INPUT type=image alt=\"Make payments with PayPal - it\'s fast, free and secure!\" src=\"https://www.paypal.com/en_US/i/btn/x-click-but04.gif\" border=0 name=submit> </FORM>]]></FullText></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 12:44:40','New version',0,1,278,1,'mattias'),(243,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[About us]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[About us]]></NavigationTitle><Leadin><![CDATA[The InfoGlue Community is a loosely organized mix of people from all over the world. Most of the people participating are doing it out of interest but some are doing it as part of their job description.]]></Leadin><FullText><![CDATA[As stated on other places we are totally independent of other companies or organisations. This is very important for us as we doubt we could keep the strict discipline of doing the best for the community instead of doing the best for individual companies. Having that said we have taken much notice of the commercial interests that exists around the platform and to make it even more widespread we feel having companies use it is the best way. Therefor we will work hard with many different activities that aim to make the platform commercially interesting. \r\n]]></FullText></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:19:48','Ny namnstandard',0,1,279,1,'mattias'),(244,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Contact information]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Contact information]]></NavigationTitle><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin><FullText><![CDATA[<p>The following ways are the best ways of getting information or personal contact with the community or individuals withing the community.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Email <a href=\"mailto:info@infoglue.org\">info@infoglue.org</a> to get in contact with the adminsitrator of this site.</li>\r\n    <li>For development questions you should use the <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(75, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">documentation</a> available on the development site.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p></p>]]></FullText></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:19:48','Ny namnstandard',0,1,280,1,'mattias'),(245,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Privacy policy]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Privacy policy]]></NavigationTitle><Leadin><![CDATA[The InfoGlue Community appreciate your interest in our products and your visit to our web site www.infoglue.org. ]]></Leadin><FullText><![CDATA[<P>To us it is important that you feel comfortable in visiting our web site. There are times when we may need information from you. Any personal information that you may give us including your e-mail address is used in the following ways: </P>\r\n<P>If you give us personal information in order to receive information in return from us we collect and store that information. That information enables us to fulfil your information request. </P>\r\n<P>If you review or download information, we track the visit. That information is helpful and give us information about which part of the site is frequented. </P>\r\n<P>The web site may contain links to other web sites. The InfoGlue Community is not responsible for the privacy practices of such web sites. You should also be aware that we use cookies on some parts of the site. </P>\r\n<P><STRONG>Legal disclaimer</STRONG> <BR>The material on this web site are provided by the InfoGlue Community as a service to our customers and may be used for informational purposes only. Although every care has been taken in compiling the information on this web site, it is provided \"as is\" without any warranties of merchantability or fitness for any particular purpose or any other warranties and representations whatsoever. Using the InfoGlue software implicates that the user accept the Gnu Public General License and that it is provided \"as is\" without any warranties of merchantability or fitness for any particular purpose or any other warranties and representations whatsoever. </P>\r\n<P>© The InfoGlue Community 2004 </P>]]></FullText></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:25','Ny namnstandard',0,1,281,1,'mattias'),(246,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Latest documentation]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Latest documentation]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<ul><li><a href=\"../../../../javadocs/docs/InfoGlue%20-%20Administrative%20Manual%20for%20version%202.6.0.pdf\" class=\"pdficon\"> InfoGlue Administrator Manual for 2.6.0 (PDF)</a></li><li><a href=\"../../../../javadocs/docs/InfoGlue%20-%20Developer%20Manual%20for%20version%202.6.0.pdf\" class=\"pdficon\">InfoGlue Developer Manual for 2.6.0 (PDF)</a></li><li><a href=\"../../../../javadocs/docs/InfoGlue%20-%20User%20Manual%20for%20version%202.6.0.pdf\" class=\"pdficon\">InfoGlue User Manual for 2.6.0 (PDF)</a></li></ul>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[<p>Latest documentation</p>]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:23','Ny namnstandard',0,1,282,1,'mattias'),(247,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Software downloads]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Software downloads]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<ul><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(35, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue CMS 2.8</a></li><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(37, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue Eclipse IDE 0.8.1</a></li><li><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(36, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">InfoGlue Calendar 1.0</a></li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[<p>Software downloads</p>]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:25','Ny namnstandard',0,1,283,1,'mattias'),(248,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Focus on your content with InfoGlue 2.8]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Focus on your content]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>We have added a lot of great new features in InfoGlue lately. Many technical improvements has been made which in themself motivate an upgrade. Having said that - we also know people miss a good example site which makes the platform less inviting. So when we started redesigning www.infoglue.org we decided to also release the complete site under the same license as InfoGlue itself.</p> <p>The benefits for you as a user are:</p> <ul>     <li>Easier to evaluate the platform</li>     <li>No need to build a lot of templates from scratch to get started, just reuse ours which is tested and built with best practices.</li>     <li>Benefit from a lot of ready made components as your site grows.</li>     <li>Copy and elaborate ideas and code from ours as long as you follow the license.</li></ul><p>As www.infoglue.org will continue to develop this means the example site will follow and be kept up to date. Whenever any new features are installed we will offer a new version publically.</p> <p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(43, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\"><img vspace=\"10\" hspace=\"10\" border=\"1\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(285, \"siteDump\")\" alt=\"screenshot infoglue.org\" style=\"\" /></a></p> <p>Read more about the site and download the repositories included <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(43, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">here</a>.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 12:44:40','New version',0,1,285,1,'mattias'),(249,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Developer pages]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Developer pages]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>This area is dedicated to all developers looking for free components, site exports and other goodies. We have started by adding the components etc used on this site.</p><p>If you got some components, tasks or sites you would like to share please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:info@infoglue.org\">info@infoglue.org</a>. The community is much dependent on contributions. It may be financial aid, software or development help.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:09','Ny namnstandard',0,1,287,1,'mattias'),(250,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Individual components]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Individual components]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>Here you can find all the components for InfoGlue.org. They are all included in the site export you can download from them sites-section. The components are not fully documented but they are being worked on and in the meantime we suspect most of you manage to read the code.</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:25','Ny namnstandard',0,1,288,1,'mattias'),(251,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Setting up a local development environment]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Setting up a local development environment]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<h2>Introduction</h2> <p>This document was written to give new developers a quick way of setting up a complete local development environment. It is important that the process is easy and we will continue to make the process easier in the future.</p> <p>This tutorial will initially describe how to get started with Eclipse as the development tool, Apache Tomcat as the servlet runner and MySQL as the database server.</p> <h2>Feedback</h2> <p>This document is always a work in progress so mail any suggestions to info@infoglue.org and I will try to improve it as the platform evolves.</p> <h2>Setting up Java</h2> <p>Download latest JDK (must be 5.x or higher) here <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp\">http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp</a> and install it. Afterwards you need to set some environment variables:</p> <h3>Linux / Unix</h3> <p>You add this to your profile or another appropriate script or run it directly on the command line:</p> <p class=\"Code\">export JAVA_HOME=&quot;/usr/local/jdk1.5.0_14&quot;<br /> export CATALINA_OPTS=&quot;-Djava.awt.headless=true -Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1 -XX:MaxPermSize=256m -Xms512M -Xmx1024M&quot;</p> <h3>Windows</h3> <p>You add two variables in Environment variables (under Control panel --&gt; System):</p> <p class=\"Code\">JAVA_HOME: c:\\Program Files\\Java\\jdk1.5.0_09<br /> CATALINA_OPTS: -Djava.awt.headless=true -Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1 -XX:MaxPermSize=256m -Xms512M -Xmx1024M</p> <h2>Setting up Tomcat</h2> <p>Fetch a late version (at least Tomcat 5.5.x) of Apache Tomcat.<br /> Get it at <a href=\"http://tomcat.apache.org\">http://tomcat.apache.org</a> -  <a href=\"http://ftp.solace.miun.se/pub/apache/tomcat/tomcat-5/v5.5.25/bin/apache-tomcat-5.5.25.zip\">http://ftp.solace.miun.se/pub/apache/tomcat/tomcat-5/v5.5.25/bin/apache-tomcat-5.5.25.zip</a> for example.</p> <p>Install it as usual and start it in console mode (on windows) so you see any errors etc in the output. If you run on linux &ndash; start it and tail catalina.out.</p> <p>Test with the browser on <a href=\"http://localhost:8080/infoglueCMS\">http://localhost:8080/infoglueCMS</a>. &nbsp;</p> <h2>Setting up MySQL</h2> <p>Download mysql here: <a href=\"http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/5.0.html#downloads\">http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/5.0.html#downloads</a></p> <p>Install as described by their document. If you want to have Unicode sites remember to state that when configuring the database.</p> <h2>Setting up Eclipse</h2> <p>This tutorial expects that you have downloaded and installed Eclipse already. It is available from <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org\">http://www.eclipse.org</a>. You must have the latest Eclipse 3.3 (Europa). We strongly suggest you download the <b><a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/download.php?file=/technology/epp/downloads/release/20071103/eclipse-jee-europa-fall2-linux-gtk.tar.gz\">Eclipse&nbsp;IDE for Java&nbsp;EE&nbsp;Developers</a>.</b></p> <p>The first thing to do is to fetch the InfoGlue projects you need from our cvs. It is done by first registering the cvs in question.</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen1\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>Switch to the CVS-view in eclipse by pressing the cvs-icon marked in red. The next view will look like this:</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen2\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>Now add a new repository location by pressing the marked button. The dialog will look like below. Use the values below and press &ldquo;Finish&rdquo; when you are done.</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen3\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>Now the repository location will be visible as below:</p> <p><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen4\")\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp;</p> <p>You can now browse the CVS by clicking on the plus-sign. Navigate to the module infoglue as below and right-click on it and select &ldquo;Check out as..&rdquo;.</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen5\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>Now you will be asked where to put the project and you can go with the default. Follow the wizard through &ndash; no need to specify much.</p> <p>After you press &ldquo;Finish&rdquo; here the project will be downloaded to your location and the project registered in eclipse. Now you can switch over to the java-view again by clicking the java-button or in the way your version of Eclipse functions.</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"eclipseScreen6\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>Now you will see the project in your left menu and you are about done.&nbsp;</p> <h2>Setting up the database</h2> <p>For InfoGlue to work it has to have a database available. The easiest way to get a database is to run the commands in the file infoglue/src/sql/developerMYSQL/developersMYSQL.sql:</p> <p><span style=\"color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\"><img src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"screeshot10\")\" alt=\"\" /></span></p> <p>You must also create a database account for the user you want to use or use the root-account which is fine also on your development environment. Look at mysql-documentation on how to do create accounts if you want a special account for InfoGlue.&nbsp;</p> <h2>Modify build.properties</h2> <p>Then you edit build.properties in the infoglue-repository to reflect your local setup. The parameters of interest are:</p> <p><img alt=\"\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(289, \"buildproperties\")\" /></p> <p>These properties are those you need to modify to reflect your local setup:</p> <p class=\"Code\">deploy.dir.shared=c:\\\\Program Files\\\\Apache Software Foundation\\\\Tomcat 5.5\\\\shared\\\\<br /> deploy.dir.cms=c:\\\\Program Files\\\\Apache Software Foundation\\\\Tomcat 5.5\\\\webapps\\\\infoglueCMS<br /> deploy.dir.working=c:\\\\Program Files\\\\Apache Software Foundation\\\\Tomcat 5.5\\\\webapps\\\\infoglueDeliverWorking<br /> <br /> database.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost/infoglue?autoReconnect=true&amp;amp;useUnicode=true&amp;amp;characterEncoding=UTF-8<br /> database.user=youruser<br /> database.password=yourpass<br /> <br /> portletBase=c:\\\\Program Files\\\\Apache Software Foundation\\\\Tomcat 5.5\\\\webapps\\\\<br /> portletBase.working=c:\\\\Program Files\\\\Apache Software Foundation\\\\Tomcat 5.5\\\\webapps\\\\<br /> <br /> mail.smtp.host=mail.mydomain.com <br /> systemEmailSender=xxxx@xxxx.xx <br /> <br /> administratorUserName=root<br /> administratorPassword=habba<br /> administratorEmail=xxxxx@xxxxx.xx</p> <p>When you save this file after modifying the settings to your environment Eclipse should build InfoGlue to the deployment directory.</p> <p>Start/Restart Tomcat and try to browse <a href=\"http://localhost:8080/infoglueCMS\">http://localhost:8080/infoglueCMS</a></p> <p>Now if everything works we suggest you also install the <a href=\"$templateLogic.getPageUrl(28, $templateLogic.languageId,-1)\">Eclipse IDE Plugin</a> for InfoGlue.&nbsp;</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:23','Ny namnstandard',0,1,289,1,'mattias'),(252,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Title><![CDATA[Sponsors]]></Title><NavigationTitle><![CDATA[Sponsors]]></NavigationTitle><FullText><![CDATA[<p>Sponsors are an important factor in all open source initiatives. We need hosting, servers and bandwidth to keep the community going. We also sometimes need sponsors for development efforts or less attractive work that needs to be done. We sometimes also need to buy services like design or translation services.</p><p>Having this said we want to present the main sponsors of InfoGlue:</p><h3>Tripnet:</h3><p><a href=\"http://www.tripnet.se\"><img border=\"0\" align=\"right\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(75, \"tripnetLogotype\")\" alt=\"\" />Tripnet</a> - have supplied our hosting since the start.&nbsp;</p><h3>Nominet UK:</h3><p><img align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(75, \"nominet\")\" /></p><p><a href=\"http://www.nominet.org.uk\">Nominet UK</a> - sponsors the documentation effort which is invaluable / critical for any software (extra thanks to Jay Daley).</p><h3>Modul 1 Data AB</h3> <p><a href=\"http://www.modul1.se\"><img width=\"160\" height=\"20\" border=\"0\" align=\"right\" alt=\"\" src=\"$templateLogic.getInlineAssetUrl(251, \"logotype\")\" />Modul 1</a> - have been a big endorser for a long time and sponsored the new site with the design (extra thanks to Kai Johansson).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>If you feel some area is neglected or you just want to help us build an even better community all contributions are welcome both financially and otherwise. Please contact us at info@infoglue.org.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>]]></FullText><Leadin><![CDATA[]]></Leadin></attributes></article>','2008-01-21 10:20:23','Ny namnstandard',0,1,291,1,'mattias'),(253,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Name><![CDATA[CSS components]]></Name></attributes></article>','2008-01-20 18:05:50','Completely new site templates',0,1,294,1,'mattias'),(254,3,'<?xml version=\'1.0\' encoding=\'UTF-8\'?><article xmlns=\'x-schema:ArticleSchema.xml\'><attributes><Template><![CDATA[#set($cl = $templateLogic.componentLogic)\r\n#set($componentContentId = $cl.infoGlueComponent.contentId)\r\n\r\nbody {\r\n	font: 62.5% \"trebuchet ms\", arial, verdana, sans-serif;\r\n	padding: 0;\r\n	margin: 0 auto;\r\n	background-color: white;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#wrapper {\r\n	widt